) of benthic groups in 11 alpine lakes.

subSection.paragraph:
Several relationships between the abundances of invertebrate taxa were found (
Table 3
). The crustacean groups were all positively correlated and oligochaetes and chironomids were positively related with crustaceans. Rotifers had higher abundances when nauplii and copepods were abundant. More tardigrades were found when nematodes and ostracods had greater densities. Significant negative relationships were found between nematodes and ostracods as well as between tardigrades and nauplii or copepods.

