subSection.paragraph:
The distribution of feeding type abundance and biomass is shown in Figure 3 . The lakes were dominated by bacterial feeders (50-92%) (
e.g., E. filiformis
,
Rhabdolaimus aquaticus
). Exceptions were found in Lake Rehbach (with 44% of omnivorous nematodes) and Lake Lautersee (with 67% of epistrate feeders, mainly
Prodesmodora circulata
). Plant ( e.g .,
Filenchus vulgaris
) and hyphal feeders ( e.g .,
Tylencholaimus sp.
) were less common. The large omnivores contributed most (53-90%) to nematode biomass in all lakes, except for Vilsalpsee and Schmalsee where epistrate feeders dominated (44-47%).

